1. What is data aggregation?  
SELECT  
COUNT(*) count,
AVG(sales) avg,
SUM(sales) sum,
MAX(sales) MAX,
MIN(sales) MIN
FROM
Sales.Orders

SELECT  
CustomerID,
COUNT(*) count,
AVG(sales) avg,
SUM(sales) sum,
MAX(sales) MAX,
MIN(sales) MIN
FROM
Sales.Orders
GROUP BY CustomerID

Window Functions Vs Aggregation functions

When using Aggregation function, will lose level of information where as using windows functions won't lose level of informaiton 
with aggregated values.

Group Aggregation :- Simple Aggregations       Window:- Aggregations + Keep Details
                   Simple Data Analysis                  Advanced Data Analysis.

--Find total sales across all orders
SELECT 
SUM(sales)
FROM
Sales.Orders

--Find total sales for each product
SELECT 
productid,
SUM(sales)
FROM
Sales.Orders
GROUP BY ProductID


--Find total sales for each product
--Additionally provide details such order id,order date
SELECT 
OrderID,
OrderDate,
productid,
SUM(sales) over(PARTITION BY productid) sum_of
FROM
Sales.Orders
